    Social Network Analysis and Recommendation


      Postdoctoral, Research Scientist position


Limited term contract : 1-year initial contract with possible extension

Deadline :  15 February 2012

Position: to start as soon as possible

Research Lab : Telecom Bretagne, LUSSI Department, Brest, France

Salary: > 33 500 Euros per year, depending on qualification and experience

http://www.telecom-bretagne.eu/ecole/ressources_humaines/offres_d_emplois/post-doc-snar-lussi/


    Description

Telecom Bretagne has an opening for a Research Scientist position to 
develop our Social Network Analysis (SNA) program. This position 
involves algorithmic theoretical studies (roughly 50%),  application 
development and code implementation. The successful candidate will work 
in collaborative projects which aim at designing, developing and 
applying scalable techniques to analyze large social networks where the 
users share contents. The work will involve social networks data mining, 
community detection, score computation, link prediction in order to 
design and develop a SNA-based Recommendation engine. The exploitation 
of a friendship network and the additional data (e.g. Annotation about 
multimedia contents, url to contents, etc.) exchanged by the users are 
not fully explored. Recent, but few, studies shows that SNA-based 
recommender systems can deal with cold-start issues and exploit the 
social relationships (social influence and selection) to infer 
similarity and predictions (see papers by Jamali et al., Golbeck, Massa 
et al., Ma et al. , Yang et al., etc.).

Work will include:

  *

    literature review about network approaches to recommendation systems

  *

    design of methods and algorithms, identification of metrics, on
    different sets of data (e.g. geolocalized video on demand logs,
    Flixster sample, social shopping network); focusing on rare contents
    and the diversity of recommendations

  *

    development and integration in projects platforms (large volume data
    framework, e.g. Mahout, MapReduce)

  *

    publications


    Team

LUSSI Department at Telecom Bretagne, member of Institut Telecom and of 
the research Lab Labsticc (UMR CNRS), is a multidisciplinary team 
working on topics such as Applied Mathematics, Computer Science, Data 
Mining but also, Sociology, Economics, etc. Two collaborative projects 
(ANR VIPEER and FUI Pay2You Places) deal with SNA-based Recommender 
Systems, but the LUSSI department is also involved in long-term research 
collaborations such as a French Chair dedicated to Social Networks in 
eMarketing and also CominLabs (an initiative selected as part of the 
« Laboratoires d'Excellence » program by the French ministry of Research 
and education). The successful candidate will then interact with other 
academic partners but also industrial partners, such as Orange (telecom 
operator) or Crédit Mutuel (bank).


    Requirements

  *

    PhD thesis in computer science

  *

    Profile:  experience in social network analysis and/or
    recommendation systems and/or  applied mathematics

  *

    Interests in applied research, strong programmation skills

  *

    Excellent English skills, proactive attitude, ability to work in a
    team, and reliability.

  *

    French speaking would be appreciated but not mandatory


    Contact

Inquiries and job application (including research statement, short CV 
and list of publications, recommendations welcome) should be sent by 
e-mail to Cécile Bothorel (cecile.bothorel [at] telecom-bretagne.eu)





-- 
Cécile Bothorel
